{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_137","type":"agent_message","text":"The swallowed failure is in `VMPluginFactory.createPlugin()`: Groovy reflectively loads `org.codehaus.groovy.vmplugin.v16.Java16` (or older plugin classes on older JDKs), catches any `Throwable`, and leaves `PLUGIN` as `null`. I’m adding constructor reflection for those VM plugin classes; that should initialize `ReflectionUtils.VM_PLUGIN` correctly and remove the bootstrap NPE."}}
